==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waterfall
<hw>Wa"ter*fall`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
fall, or perpendicular descent, of the water of a river or stream, or a
descent nearly perpendicular; a cascade; a cataract.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Hairdressing)</fld> <def>An arrangement of a
woman's back hair over a cushion or frame in some resemblance to a
waterfall.</def><-- = a fall? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A certain kind of neck scarf.</def> <rj><au>T.
Hughes.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water feather-foil</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Water feather</ent>⟦br⟧
